s11 = 11 | goals11 = 1\n| years12  = 2018\u20132019     | clubs12  = [[FC Atyrau|Atyrau]]                         | caps12 = 16  | goals12 = 0\n| years13  = 2019       | clubs13  = [[MFK Fr\u00fddek-M\u00edstek|Fr\u00fddek-M\u00edstek]]        | caps13 =    | goals13 =  \n| years14  = 2020\u2013     | clubs14  = [[FC Petr\u017ealka]]                         | caps14 = 0  | goals14 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2007\u20132008 | nationalteam1 = [[Slovakia national under-19 football team|Slovakia U19]] | nationalcaps1 = 9 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2011\u2013     | nationalteam2 = [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]]              | nationalcaps2 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0\n| club-update = 6 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 4 September 2016\n}}\n'''Franti\u0161ek Kub\u00edk''' (born 14 March 1989) is a [[Slovakia|Slovak]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|winger]] or a [[Defender (association football)|left back]] for [[FC Petr\u017ealka]].\n\n==Club career==\nKub\u00edk started his career in hometown club [[FK Mesto Prievidza|HFK Prievidza]]. In winter 2008, he  moved to the [[Slovak First League|Second Division]] club [[FK AS Tren\u010d\u00edn|AS Tren\u010d\u00edn]]. In summer 2009, ADO coach [[John van den Brom]] noticed Kub\u00edk at pre-season football tournament in the [[Netherlands]]. After a year he has signed one-year loan for [[ADO Den Haag]]. He made his ADO debut against [[Vitesse Arnhem]] on 8 August 2010 and first goal scored against [[Roda JC]] on 15 August 2010. He overall scored 9 goals in [[2010\u201311 Eredivisie|2010\u201311]], 8 in Eredivisie and 1 in the [[2010\u201311 Eredivisie#European competition|European competition play-off]].\n\nOn 5 June 2011, Kub\u00edk signed 4-year contract for [[Russia]]n club [[FC Kuban Krasnodar|FC Kuban]]. He made his Kuban debut in a 5\u20130 win against [[FC Volga Nizhny Novgorod|FC Volga]] on 21 August 2011. He played for Kuban only 5 matches and was transferred to [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] club [[SC Tavriya Simferopol]] on 12 February 2012.\n\n==International career==\nHe made his debut for the [[Slovakia national football team]] in [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] on 9 February 2011.\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|frantisek-kubik/137122}}\n* {{in lang|nl}} [http://www.vi.nl/Spelers/Speler.htm?dbid=66767&typeofpage=84137 Voetbal International]\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kubik, Frantisek}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Slovak footballers]]\n[[Category:Slovakia international footballers]]\n[[Category:AS Tren\u010d\u00edn players]]\n[[Category:ADO Den Haag players]]\n[[Category:\u0160K Slovan Bratislava players]]\n[[Category:M\u0160K \u017dilina players]]\n[[Category:FC Kuban Krasnodar players]]\n[[Category:SC Tavriya Simferopol players]]\n[[Category:FC Arsenal Kyiv players]]\n[[Category:Ergotelis F.C. players]]\n[[Category:FC Atyrau players]]\n[[Category:MFK Fr\u00fddek-M\u00edstek players]]\n[[Category:FC Petr\u017ealka players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Russian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Slovak expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Russia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Kazakhstan]]\n[[Category:Slovak expatriate sportspeople in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Slovak expatriate sportspeople in Russia]]\n[[Category:People from Prievidza]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name              = Franti\u0161ek Kub\u00edk\n| fullname          = Franti\u0161ek Kub\u00edk\n| image             = Franti\u0161ek Kub\u00edk.jpg\n| image_size        = 200\n| caption           =\n| birth_date        = {{birth date and age|d