ww.gutenberg.org/etext/12410 |publisher=Project Gutenberg |date=May 1, 2004 |accessdate=April 2, 2011}}\n* [[Olivier Weber]], ''Sur les routes de la soie'' (On the Silk Roads) (with [[Reza Deghati|Reza]]), Ho\u00ebbeke, 2007\n* {{cite book|title=Daughter of Xanadu|last=Yang|first=Dori Jones|authorlink=Dori Jones Yang|publisher=Delacorte Press Books for Young Readers|year=2011|isbn=978-0-385-73923-8|url=https://archive.org/details/daughterofxanadu00yang}} (Young Adult novel)\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category|Marco Polo}}\n{{wikisource author}}\n{{Wikivoyage|On the trail of Marco Polo}}\n* {{curlie|Society/History/By_Topic/Exploration/Explorers/Polo,_Marco/|Marco Polo}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170428114043/http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0026847/ Marco Polo] on [[IMDb]]\n* [http://www.innvenice.com/Marco-Polo.htm Marco Polo's house in Venice, near the church of San Giovanni Grisostomo]\n* [http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/ngm/data/2001/07/01/sights_n_sounds/media.2.2.html National Geographic Marco Polo: Journey from Venice to China]\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=Polo,+Marco | name=Marco Polo}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Marco Polo}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=6353}}\n\n{{Notable foreigners who visited China}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Polo, Marco}}\n[[Category:Marco Polo| ]]\n[[Category:1254 births]]\n[[Category:1324 deaths]]\n[[Category:13th-century explorers]]\n[[Category:13th-century Venetian people]]\n[[Category:13th-century Venetian writers]]\n[[Category:14th-century Venetian people]]\n[[Category:Explorers of Asia]]\n[[Category:Explorers of Central Asia]]\n[[Category:Explorers from the Republic of Venice]]\n[[Category:Medieval travel writers]]\n[[Category:People from Venice]]\n[[Category:Republic of Venice merchants]]\n[[Category:Republic of Venice writers]]\n[[Category:Venetian expatriates in China]]\n[[Category:Venetian male writers]]\n[[Category:Venetian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Venetian travel writers]]\